| **Team Name**                                                         | Backup                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
| **Automation Theme**                                                  | Automated Backup Failure Detection and Incident Management                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            |
| **Problem Statement**                                                 | - Cohesity provides native backup failure visibility through UI, alerts, and failure reports. <br>- These inputs still require operational correlation to identify which failures are currently unresolved. <br>- Failures need validation to confirm whether a later successful backup has cleared the issue. <br>- ServiceNow tracking also needs to be checked separately to avoid duplicate or missed incident handling. <br>- The challenge is not visibility alone; it is consolidated validation, incident tracking, and consistent follow-up for active backup failures.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |
| **Current Impact**                                                    | - Backup alerts are received by email, but acting on every alert individually can create noise and duplicate checks. <br>- Some failures are cleared by later retries, so immediate incident updates without validation can be inaccurate. <br>- The team still needs to consolidate alerts, validate latest backup status, check ServiceNow, and track unresolved failures separately. <br>- This creates manual effort and possible detection gaps between scheduled reviews.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |
| **Proposed Automation Solution**                                      | **Two interrelated controls support the same backup failure process:** <br><br>**1. Dynatrace Workflow – Scheduled Failure Detection and Incident Flow** <br>- Uses a **24-hour backup failure compute window**. <br>- Checks Cohesity backup failures using API-based logic. <br>- Validates whether each failure remains unresolved or is cleared by a later successful backup. <br>- Searches ServiceNow for the active backup failure incident. <br>- Creates one ServiceNow incident when unresolved backup failures are identified. <br>- Updates the same incident every 4 hours with the latest unresolved failure details. <br>- Sends email reports with current failure details for visibility and follow-up. <br>- Incident investigation, owner follow-up, remediation updates, and closure remain manual after operational review. <br><br>**2. PowerShell Script – On-Demand Validation Flow** <br>- Provides menu-driven validation for ad-hoc checks. <br>- Supports workload-specific execution for **VM, SQL, Oracle, or All** backup types. <br>- Supports multi-run validation depending on the selected workload scope. <br>- Supports verbose mode to show what the script is currently processing. <br>- Supports silent mode for quick validation output. <br>- Provides an interim validation control when email alerts indicate new failures or increased failure volume before the next Dynatrace update. |
| **Why Immediate Action on Every Email Alert Is Not Always Practical** | - Email alerts provide early notification, but they are not always consolidated with latest backup retry status. <br>- A failure may be cleared by a later successful backup, so validation is needed before incident updates. <br>- Dynatrace provides the structured incident workflow and recurring updates. <br>- PowerShell provides immediate ad-hoc validation when email alerts require faster confirmation.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| **Smart Control Logic**                                               | - The solution does not blindly report every backup failure. <br>- It checks whether a newer successful backup exists after the failure. <br>- Only unresolved failures are carried forward. <br>- Duplicate incident creation is avoided by updating the same active ServiceNow incident. <br>- Manual follow-up remains with the operations team for investigation, owner updates, remediation notes, and closure.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| **Tools Used**                                                        | Dynatrace Workflow, Cohesity APIs, Dynatrace Credential Vault, ServiceNow Incident Integration, Email Alerts/Reports, PowerShell                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |
